The deputy head of the CS Information Security Department, Artem Sychev, said that a wide range of Russian banks had encountered the replacement of the number.
He explained that operators did not always respond to the Central Bank's warnings of fraud calls because of the absence of such a duty in the Communications Act.
At the Open Bank, Rosbanke and the Alpha bank confirmed an increase in the number of cheating calls with a number swap.
As reported by the Bilaya press, some of the information about the fraud that was handed over to the CB was incorrect: the lists included numbers that were actually used by banks to communicate with customers.
